verbose_text: We posit that the missense changes present in both subjects do not alter the amount of ATP5F1D but instead lead to an inability of ATP5F1D to bind other F 1 subunits correctly and thus result in reduced assembly of complex V. To assess mitochondrial morphology, we performed transmission electron microscopy (TEM) on cultured skin fibroblasts of subject 1 (XREF_FIG A).
